properties.headline: SCHEDULED ROADWORK Pedestrian & cyclist bridge removal - ROZELLE Anzac Bridge at Victoria Rd and The Crescent
properties.publicTransport: Buses between the city and Inner West will be diverting via The Crescent and through Glebe. Check transportnsw.info travel alerts for more details.
properties.otherAdvice:
Major closures will be in place on the Anzac Bridge between 9pm Saturday 5 September and 8am Sunday 6 September to allow for the removal of the overhead pedestrian and cyclist Beatrice Bush Bridge at Victoria Rd.

Motorists should avoid unnecessary travel through the area and use Parramatta Rd to travel between the city and Inner West during these times.

Motorists from the Northern suburbs should consider using Epping Rd and the Sydney Harbour Bridge.

Some lanes on the Anzac Bridge will start closing from 8pm, with all lanes to reopen by 10am on Sunday.

From 9pm: 2 lanes eastbound and 3 lanes westbound will be closed on the Anzac Bridge. Motorists can travel across the bridge in both directions using the citybound lanes, however significant delays are expected and motorists should use Parramatta Rd. 

From 1am: closure of all westbound lanes on the Anzac Bridge from the city and all eastbound lanes from Victoria Rd. One eastbound lane on City West Link across the Anzac Bridge remains open however delays are expected.

Motorists from Victoria Rd will be diverted via The Crescent and through Glebe for access to Pyrmont, the city or to rejoin the Western Distributor.

From 5.30am: 2 lanes eastbound and 3 lanes westbound will be closed on the Anzac Bridge. Motorists can travel across the bridge in both directions using the citybound lanes, however significant delays are expected and motorists should use Parramatta Rd.

From 8am until approximately 10am some lane closures will remain in place on the Anzac Bridge.
